author: Dr. Angela N. Baldwin
title: COVID-19 symptoms may include altered senses of smell, taste
description: "Without adequate testing, I don't think you can know for sure" whether altered senses of taste and smell are because of novel coronavirus, a doctor told ABC News.
content: Doctors and researchers still have much to learn about the exact symptoms caused by COVID-19, but a group of ear, nose and throat doctors now suspect two such symptoms may be an altered sense of taste, called dysgeusia, and a loss of smell, known as anosmia.… [+3713 chars]
